  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>aubergine[s]</strong> and<strong> courgette[s]</strong> lengthways</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced aubergine </strong>and<strong> courgette </strong>to a baking tray (or two!) with your<strong> ras el hanout</strong>, a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until everything is cooked through and tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2229Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2229Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2229Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2229Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2229Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a medium-sized pot over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pistachio nuts</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk so they don't burn!</p><p>Once toasted, transfer to a plate and set aside for later and reserve the pot</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2229Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2229Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2229Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2229Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2229Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse your <strong>quinoa</strong> in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>quinoa</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 6-8 min or until all the quinoa is tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot until serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2229Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2229Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2229Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2229Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2229Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the quinoa is cooking, peel and finely grate (or finely chop) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Roll your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2229Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
